## 7. Summary of Architectural Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| **Extend existing saga** vs. new saga | Maintains transaction unity; stipend disbursement and auto-payment are logically coupled |
| **Query projections for eligibility** | CQRS pattern: read models are optimized for queries; avoid hitting the write model |
| **Consent as first-class entity** | FERPA compliance requires auditable consent records; not a simple boolean flag |
| **Step 5 is non-blocking** | Auto-payment failure should not fail the stipend disbursement (student still gets money) |
| **Compensating action reverses ledger entry** | Saga pattern requires idempotent compensation; ledger reversal creates compensating entries |
| **New projector for student balances** | Separation of concerns; dashboard KPIs vs. individual student account views |

